'''Libya–Malaysia relations''' ({{lang-ar|العلاقات الليبية الماليزية}} {{transl|ar|alealaqat alliybiat almalizia}}; {{lang-ms|Hubungan Libya–Malaysia}}; [[Jawi alphabet|Jawi]]: هوبوڠن ليبيا–مليسيا) refers to [[bilateralism|bilateral]] [[diplomacy|foreign relations]] between [[Libya]] and [[Malaysia]]. Libya has an embassy in [[Kuala Lumpur]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://libyanembassy.my/|title=Libyan Embassy in Malaysia|publisher=Embassy of Libya|accessdate=3 February 2018}}</ref> and Malaysia has an embassy in [[Tripoli]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kln.gov.my/web/lby_tripoli/|title=Official Website of Embassy of Malaysia, Tripoli|publisher=[[Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Malaysia]]|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref>

== History ==
Since the new Libyan government period, the relations between the two countries has been enhance when Malaysia recognise the new government of [[National Transitional Council]] as the interim government of Libya on 26 August 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://my.news.yahoo.com/malaysia-recognises-ntc-libyas-interim-government-152635043.html|title=Malaysia Recognises National Transitional Council As Libya's Interim Government|date=26 August 2011|work=[[Bernama]]|publisher=[[Yahoo! News]]|accessdate=3 May 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503094242/https://my.news.yahoo.com/malaysia-recognises-ntc-libyas-interim-government-152635043.html|archivedate=3 May 2014|deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.asiaone.com/News/AsiaOne+News/Malaysia/Story/A1Story20110826-296305.html |title=Libyan embassy raises new flag |work=New Straits Times |publisher=[[AsiaOne]] |date=26 August 2011 |accessdate=3 May 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503095806/http://news.asiaone.com/News/AsiaOne%2BNews/Malaysia/Story/A1Story20110826-296305.html |archivedate= 3 May 2014 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>

== Economic relations ==
Currently, Libya looks Malaysia as a model to expand their country economy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theborneopost.com/2013/03/18/libyan-envoy-seeks-msian-assistance-to-revive-economy/|title=Libyan envoy seeks M’sian assistance to revive economy|publisher=[[The Borneo Post]]|work=Bernama|date=18 March 2013|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref><ref name="le">{{cite web|url=http://www.smemagazine.asia/index.php/top-news/malaysia/1533-libya-seeks-malaysian-help-to-revive-economy|title=Libya Seeks Malaysian Help to Revive Economy|publisher=SME Magazine|date=18 March 2013|accessdate=3 May 2014|author=Adrian|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503113512/http://www.smemagazine.asia/index.php/top-news/malaysia/1533-libya-seeks-malaysian-help-to-revive-economy|archivedate=3 May 2014|deadurl=yes}}</ref> At present, there are six Malaysian [[fossil fuel|oil and gas]] companies operation in Libya and the country is now seek Malaysia for more investment to develop their country since the country destroy in [[2011 Libyan Civil War|Libyan Civil War]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://libya.tv/en/libya-seeks-further-investment-from-malaysia/|title=Libya seeks further investment from Malaysia|publisher=[[Libya TV]]|date=18 March 2013|accessdate=3 May 2014|author=[http://libya.tv/en/author/sdhaimish/ Sherif Dhaimish]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503111152/http://libya.tv/en/libya-seeks-further-investment-from-malaysia/|archivedate=3 May 2014|deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref name="le"/> An [[Bilateral air transport agreement|agreement on air services]] were signed in 2009 and both countries agreed to formalise a [[memorandum of understanding]] on airlines.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tripolipost.com/articledetail.asp?c=2&i=3843|title=Libya, Malaysia to Sign Air Services Agreement|publisher=[[Tripoli Post]]|work=Bernama|date=12 December 2009|accessdate=3 May 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503112802/http://www.tripolipost.com/articledetail.asp?c=2&i=3843|archivedate=3 May 2014|deadurl=yes}}</ref> Libya also seeks co-operation with Malaysia in [[Islamic banking]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theedgemalaysia.com/business-news/276157-libya-seeks-more-cooperation-with-malaysia-in-islamic-banking.html |title=Libya seeks more cooperation with Malaysia in Islamic banking |publisher=[[The Edge (Malaysia)|The Edge]] |work=Bernama |date=19 February 2014 |accessdate=3 May 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503115256/http://www.theedgemalaysia.com/business-news/276157-libya-seeks-more-cooperation-with-malaysia-in-islamic-banking.html |archivedate= 3 May 2014 |df= }}</ref>

== Education relations ==
In education, approximately 1,000–1,200 Malaysian students are sponsored by the Libyan government to studied in Libya while 2,000 Libyan students will coming to Malaysia to do a [[vocational education|vocational training]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bharian.com.my/bharian/articles/MalaysiadestinasipelajarLibya-Duta/Article/index_html|title=Malaysia destinasi pelajar Libya - Duta|language=Malay|publisher=[[Berita Harian]]| work=Bernama|date=20 February 2014|accessdate=3 May 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503155434/http://www.bharian.com.my/bharian/articles/MalaysiadestinasipelajarLibya-Duta/Article/index_html|archivedate=3 May 2014|deadurl=yes}}</ref>

